A jet of flames burst from Thassalin's jaws as the colossal Thraki ignited a precise patch of the forest, then flew in a circle above, observing him for a time. Curiously, as he had slowed, the strange cries of laughter behind him had stopped. Thassalin had forgotten that he had passengers on his back.
"Come on, Tenuk, you've already transformed into Thraki!"
"Mine is a very different flight. I don't let myself be lifted abruptly by a huge pink dragon!"
"Isn't it not so unpleasant, Kayel?"
Kayel was clearly not in agreement with Nyssi, he seemed less black than usual and had planted his claws into the back of Thassalin, to the point that he had made Thraki bleed, but it was evident that he didn't care much. However, Thassalin had realized that he had terrorized his new friends and had found a clearing where to land.
"My apologies, I SMELL SOMETHING. I SHOULD HAVE CHECKED."
"Didn't you have to drag us along with you?", Tenuk shouted as he slid down the back of Thassalin. "And we left Retvik behind! We abandoned our great and strong fighter! How will he catch up with us?"
"He'll find a way," Nissy retorted. "Retvik is slow, but not stupid."
"He'll find a way," Nissy retorted. "Retvik is slow, but not stupid."
"He blinked his eyes and turned back to Tenuk. "Of course he knows how to drive.""
"Have you ever seen Retvik driving a vehicle? He doesn't have a truck like yours, and I've never seen him drive anything like Kayel's cute little car either, and if he started coming to work in a car, it's only because YOU drove us there. He's just got a bike."
A burst of laughter interrupted them. Thassalin was suddenly overcome with hilarity, and no one understood what was making him laugh. It took him a bit too long to regain his composure.
"I'm sorry, but I imagined your big friend in armor on a tiny Temthan bike meant for kids. It was so funny! I wish I had telepathy. What a precious thought that I couldn't share!"
Kayel chuckled, imagining what Thassalin was thinking. "Yes, that's just it. But what did you pick up and why did you take off so quickly?"
Thassalin groaned, took off and disappeared briefly, before returning and dropping a carcass in front of Nyssi. It was an Orothrack, a golden and white dragon-like creature, very rare. But it was missing its head. "ANOTHER DEATH. I HEAR THEIR CRIES. I FEEL THEIR BLOOD. I AM PROGRAMMED TO PROTECT AND HUNT. AS YISINI COMMANDS. CREATURES ARE NEAR."
The mighty Thraki froze suddenly. Nyssi and Kayel did too, their attention drawn to a gap in the clearing. Whatever it was, this thing was huge and black, hissing. Whatever it was, this thing spread two colossal pairs of wings and charged straight at Thassalin, not minding the three smaller beings in its path. Kayel and Tenuk just managed to get out of the way in time, but Nyssi was swept up and almost thrown onto Thassalin.
Thassalin reacted to the attack by grabbing Nissy and throwing her onto his back, using his extraordinary long and agile tail, before taking off. The black creature with two wings quickly gave chase.
Kayel took a deep breath, unshouldering the rifle he had at his back, then opened a pouch that contained a cartridge belt. He put it around his waist so he could easily access it, but soon realized that Nyssi, the Thraki, and the monster were no longer in sight.
"Yes, that would be great, Tenuk, could you transform into something that flies?"
"Do you want to chase after them?"
"Yes, of course!"
"But... one of them is a giant monster!"
"And then? I've got a super powerful rifle in my hands right now, ready to serve. I just need to see it to shoot it down."
Tenuk hesitated, then stepped back to clear some space. With a weak, slightly pained growl, his body unfolded, his fur replaced by scales, and his arms transformed into wings. He quickly returned to his normal clear blue Thraki form, but his eyes remained red.
"Get on."
Having regained a more normal Thraki appearance, Tenuk now had his back covered in scaly plates, but a pair of spikes had also grown there, making it convenient for Kayel to hold on. Tenuk took a little time to take off, but once in the air, he quickly oriented himself and attempted to pursue.
However, Tenuk and Kayel soon realized they were not alone. A second dark creature emerged from below, and Tenuk narrowly avoided it.
I suppose it's the other big scary beast that was worrying Lanex? Kayel furrowed his brow trying to shoot the second beast, missed his target and quickly reloaded his rifle.
Tenuk didn't react. He was too focused on flying towards Nyssi and Thassalin, despite the other creature in pursuit. Kayel awkwardly spun around himself to face the monster. The fact that it was chasing them was a boon for Kayel, as it made it easier for him to target and shoot. Two shots passed through the upper wings of the creature, which let out a cry of pain as it disappeared again under the trees. Kayel wasn't sure if it was still following them, but it wouldn't be able to catch up.
Further on, Nyssi desperately clung on, while Thassalin flew in a circle, launching bursts of flames at the blackened monster. Although the creature was clearly wounded, it seemed furious and determined to engage, and the fireballs seemed to have no intended effect. When Thassalin righted himself, Nyssi took the opportunity to draw her gun, a reliable rifle. It wasn't of course designed for this kind of situation, but a salvo of shots would surely at least deter the black beast, wouldn't they?
